My laptop charger stopped working
Issue Description:
My laptop charger died. The light on the brick is off and my laptop won't charge at all. The battery is draining and I'll be stuck soon. Can I get a new charger?

Troubleshooting performed:
- Tried a different outlet
- Wiggled the cable
- No charging light at all


How to resolve this
1 - Over Team Chat, confirm the charger (not the laptop) is the problem: no charging light, laptop runs on battery. Have them try another outlet if they haven't
2 - Ask the user for their shipping address
3-Open Tools → Ship Manager, enter their address, select "Laptop Charger", set Rush Priority (Instant) and click Ship
4-When it arrives, have them plug it in and confirm it's charging
5-They confirm charging — resolve

Summary
A dead charger with a healthy laptop is the simplest hardware-replacement ticket: confirm the charger is the fault, ship the correct replacement charger to the user, and confirm it charges. No device replacement needed.

ticket closed 
